54Z","updated_at":"2018-02-07T07:00:50Z","closed_at":"2017-02-06T10:27:16Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"```\r\n[ZYPSC] 03:41:31 INFO: Single thread SHA256 performance is 559 MB/s using minio/sha256-simd (10 MB/s using crypto/sha256).\r\n[ZYPSC] 03:41:33 INFO: Actual hashing performance is 84.14 MB/s\r\n```\r\n\r\nWeak hashing slows the actual hashing down almost an order of magnitude. It seems there is no hardware acceleration for it. I'm not sure what the requirements for a weak hash function are, but it could be much faster if it's hardware accelerated.\r\n\r\nAccording to  `/proc/cpuinfo`, these features are supported:\r\n```\r\nFeatures        : fp asimd evtstrm aes pmull sha1 sha2 crc32\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe we can use one of those for the weak hash?\r\n\r\n### Version Information\r\n\r\n    Syncthing Version: v0.14.21\r\n    Android Version: Android 7.0\r\n    Device: LG G4 (Snapdragon 808)","closed_by":{"login":"st-review","id":16196517,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTk2NTE3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16196517?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review","html_url":"https://github.com/st-review","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/st-review/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users